# Privacy Policy
*Last Updated: March 9, 2026*

## 1. Introduction
I value your privacy and am committed to protecting your personal data. This policy outlines how I handle your information when you visit my website or engage my services for web, app, or custom software development.

## 2. Data I Collect
As a single developer, I only collect the minimum amount of data necessary to provide my services:

- **Contact Information:** Name, email address, and your message you provide via my contact form or email.
- **Anonymous Browser Data:** Anonymous data about your browser and device, used to improve my website.
- **Anonymous Browsing Data:** Anonymous data about the pages you visit on my website, used to improve my website.

This data is not linked to any personal information and is used solely for the purpose of improving my website.

## 3. How I Use Your Data
I use your information strictly for:
- Communicating with you regarding your inquiries or active projects.
- Improving the user experience of my website.
- Analytics and statistics about my website.

## 4. Data Storage & Security
I implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data.

- **Infrastructure:** My website is hosted via a secure provider.
- **Third Parties:** I may use trusted third-party services for hosting or analytics. These providers have their own strict privacy standards.

## 5. Data Sharing
I do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. I only share data when necessary to:
- Comply with legal obligations.

## 6. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you have the following rights:
- **Access:** Request a copy of the data I hold about you.
- **Correction:** Request that I fix any inaccurate information.
- **Deletion:** Request that I delete your personal data.

## 7. Contact Me
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact me at:
- **Email:** Not available at the moment, for questions use the contact form or contact me via my social media.
- **Company:** dotsem
